        <div id="poetry">
            <h2>Poetry</h2>
            <div class="flex-centered">
                <p>
                    <strong>My Name</strong><br><br>
                    Like the flower.<br>
                    Like the Latin nominative, <em>star</em>, one I plucked<br>
                    from the silent soil of night<br>
                    and pressed to paper<br>
                    with a scrawl.<br>
                    Thin petals of light twinkle in my eye,<br>
                    and seeds of smiles sprout<br>
                    when the bloom of it<br>
                    beams upon your lips:<br><br>             
                    <em>"Aster."</em><br><br>
                    Say it again,<br>
                    let its sound powder over me;<br>
                    sprinkle my ears with stardust;<br>
                    I've flower-crowned myself with<br>
                    the power of choosing<br>
                    so every utterance is an honoring;<br>
                    each inscription glitters and glows.<br>
                    It grows from the discarded husk of<br>
                    <em>unchosen</em>,<br>
                    a cultivated choice<br>
                    rooting in the firmament<br>
                    of my being,<br>
                    so let it blossom:<br>
                    say it again.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
